history.content: Because of recent trends in EE16B with juniors/seniors having enrollment issues, I'd absolutely recommend you get that class done asap while there are spots reserved for you. I delayed 61C and 170 to my junior year, and I feel like of the two, 170 is a better class workload wise and more helpful to take early so it helps you with recruiting and all.

I'm thinking about either taking ee16b and cs61c or taking cs61c and cs170 and the third class I will take in fall 2021. I heard cs170 is good to take for recruiting, but I'm wondering if I should just try to get ee16b done asap (currently a sophomore btw). If I take cs170 in the fall, will it be enough for recruiting to be taking the class concurrently or should I also be prepping during the summer?

Also I was wondering if I should phase 2 any of these classes for space for a breadth. Thank you!
history.subject: CS61c, CS170, or EE16b
